          <source>Row Error Information</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To avoid having to respond to row errors while editing values in a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Data.DataTable&gt;</ph>, you can add the error information to the row for later use.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Data.DataRow&gt;</ph> object provides a <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Data.DataRow.RowError%2A&gt;</ph> property on each row for this purpose.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Adding data to the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>RowError<ept id="p1">**</ept> property of a <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>DataRow<ept id="p2">**</ept> sets the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Data.DataRow.HasErrors%2A&gt;</ph> property of the <bpt id="p3">**</bpt>DataRow<ept id="p3">**</ept> to <bpt id="p4">**</bpt>true<ept id="p4">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>DataRow<ept id="p1">**</ept> is part of a <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>DataTable<ept id="p2">**</ept>, and <bpt id="p3">**</bpt>DataRow.HasErrors<ept id="p3">**</ept> is <bpt id="p4">**</bpt>true<ept id="p4">**</ept>, the <bpt id="p5">**</bpt>DataTable.HasErrors<ept id="p5">**</ept> property is also <bpt id="p6">**</bpt>true<ept id="p6">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This applies as well to the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>DataSet<ept id="p1">**</ept> to which the <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>DataTable<ept id="p2">**</ept> belongs.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>When testing for errors, you can check the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>HasErrors<ept id="p1">**</ept> property to determine if error information has been added to any rows.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>HasErrors<ept id="p1">**</ept> is <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>true<ept id="p2">**</ept>, you can use the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Data.DataTable.GetErrors%2A&gt;</ph> method of the <bpt id="p3">**</bpt>DataTable<ept id="p3">**</ept> to return and examine only the rows with errors, as shown in the following example.</source>
        </trans-unit>
